>> Examples

An example of methods as statements.

<pre>
Class GameObject

	Field x:Float
	Field y:Float

	Method PrintX ()
		Print x
	End

	Method PrintY ()
		Print y
	End

End

Local g:GameObject = New GameObject

p.x = 100
p.y = 200

' Accessing method...

p.PrintX
p.PrintY
</pre>

Strict mode version of above GameObject class. (Note use of Void return type.)

